        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: \"1-Day Lisbon Itinerary: The Best Plan for First-Time Visitors\"\nurl: \"https://thetourguy.com/travel-blog/portugal/lisbon/1-day-lisbon-itinerary/\"\ndescription: \"This plan hits the essentials, but you can tweak it depending on your style: Food lovers: Swap the morning tuk tuk tour for a Lisbon Food and Sightseeing Tuk Tuk Tour to combine local eats with iconic sights.\"\npage_age: \"January 27, 2026\"\nprofile_name: The Tour Guy\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/_diWKJVMuk1-n8wxKNtRtm9_Q2oxiV0Ew64BVwtqo-A/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvODBmNzAwNTMx/MmY3ZTAxODM0YjAw/ZWEwMjJlMjhhNDdk/M2NjY2ZjNmZhZjBj/NzdhYzFkOTRkMjRi/MmI3Mjc4OS90aGV0/b3VyZ3V5LmNvbS8\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/Xz79s6ywZv2g_ptdJegmVxdb4KrcYm9gs6sB2UQavcA/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly90aGV0/b3VyZ3V5LmNvbS93/cC1jb250ZW50L3Vw/bG9hZHMvMjAyNi8w/MS9saXNib24tMS1k/YXktaXRpbmVyYXJ5/LUZJLmpwZw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://thetourguy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/lisbon-1-day-itinerary-FI.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"If it’s your first time in Lisbon and you want to see the highlights without climbing every hill, this 1-day itinerary is for you. You’ll get a full sense of the city’s character, including historic neighborhoods, riverfront landmarks, and famous viewpoints, while leaving time to relax and enjoy a sunset sail on the Tagus.|This itinerary has you out and about all day, so be sure to bring a hat and sunscreen for the afternoon in Belem and an extra layer for the cruise. This plan hits the essentials, but you can tweak it depending on your style: Food lovers: Swap the morning tuk tuk tour for a Lisbon Food and Sightseeing Tuk Tuk Tour to combine local eats with iconic sights.|You will glide up Lisbon’s hills effortlessly, pause at the city’s best viewpoints, and explore streets that buses and cars cannot reach. This is the quickest and most scenic way to understand the city’s layout and history. Insider tip: Wear shoes you can step out in for a few quick photo stops, and don’t be shy. Ask your guide to point out hidden gems along the way! Finish your tuk tuk ride near Time Out Market and grab lunch from one of Lisbon’s top chefs under one roof.|Home > travel-blog > Portugal > Lisbon > 1-Day Lisbon Itinerary: The Best Plan for First-Time Visitors\"\nhash: 7748728e77cf136b\nembed_ref: thetourguy.com-N05\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
