        "type": "website",
        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: \"How to Spend 1 Day in Lisbon, Portugal: Highlights, Culture, and Iconic Eats\"\nurl: \"https://periodicadventures.com/1-day-in-lisbon-portugal-itinerary/\"\ndescription: \"The view from up here is insanely beautiful. Worth the trek! For lunch, I recommend Taberna dos Ferreiros where they serve traditional Portuguese dishes like bacalhau, which is salted cod.\"\npage_age: \"October 31, 2024\"\nprofile_name: Periodic Adventures\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/O5g3MxWBZ1231_Ct2jNvU-j5xbnvozU2qmvv0MIJY-Y/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMjBhY2RkYzEz/MjhiMDEzZDQ2ZTgy/YzQwN2JhNWVjZTZk/NzI3ZmY1ZTYxMmM1/ODgwYTAzMDZlMjc0/OGY5YWEzMy9wZXJp/b2RpY2FkdmVudHVy/ZXMuY29tLw\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/bK_LcpAswt1vg3TUFG8kwSOh4OU5dHyoceG8yFQyr7s/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9wZXJp/b2RpY2FkdmVudHVy/ZXMuY29tL3dwLWNv/bnRlbnQvdXBsb2Fk/cy8yMDI0LzA0L1Nh/bnRhLUp1c3RhLUxp/ZnQtTGlzYm9uLXNj/YWxlZC5qcGc\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://periodicadventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Santa-Justa-Lift-Lisbon-scaled.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"So, without further ado, here’s how to spend 1 day in Lisbon, Portugal including the historic Alfama district, a walking tour to see all the highlights, and stops for the most iconic food in the city! ... Psssst before we dive in, just had to let you know that I created a quick 1-page download of this itinerary for easy reference later.|Take them up or down for viewpoints of the city. That’s where the Santa Justa Lift connects. It’s impossible to miss! The view from up here is insanely beautiful. Worth the trek! For lunch, I recommend Taberna dos Ferreiros where they serve traditional Portuguese dishes like bacalhau, which is salted cod. Alternatively, Roger’s Restaurante has pizza and is within walking distance of our dessert stop, which is really the star of the show this afternoon.|Pasteis de Belem is a staple in Lisbon! This afternoon, assuming you haven’t eaten too many egg tarts and can still walk, I’m taking you to the Monument to the Discoveries first.|Only because there’s so much to see in Lisbon and if you only have a day, we’ve got to make it count. Still, I wanted to tell you about it and give you the option in case you’re reading this like, “yesssss, a castle…let me at it!” · Before you leave Alfama, don’t miss Miradouro da Graça. Pro tip: Miradouro means “viewpoint” in Portuguese, so if you see a Miradouro sign, that means there’s a great view in that direction.\"\nhash: 367d685442ce377a\nembed_ref: periodicadventures.com-IKi\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
