        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: 22 Must-Do Things in Lisbon for First Timers - Bon Traveler\nurl: \"https://www.bontraveler.com/things-to-do-in-lisbon-portugal/\"\ndescription: \"On Saturday and Sunday afternoons, the place is a good spot to hear amateur singers who are getting established. Any occasion is a good one to enjoy a bifana, a grilled thinly sliced pork that is unique to Lisbon’s food culture.\"\npage_age: \"May 29, 2025\"\nprofile_name: Bon Traveler\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/A6DVHsHL3MUB2A4aCkduweHf19HsL5MQqeWoRa1xh34/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvNWM3MWM5ZTMy/ZWI4YmU1NDFkNzU2/YWZjYzUzMDIyZWZk/MGEyNThhN2JkN2Ri/ZDY0NzdiMmJhNTNh/ZTFkYTMxNi93d3cu/Ym9udHJhdmVsZXIu/Y29tLw\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/VVjj5jxcWCPZ_ydJr-XvpKcxhBvKQd0kKoGMsod_8Ik/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/Ym9udHJhdmVsZXIu/Y29tL3dwLWNvbnRl/bnQvdXBsb2Fkcy8y/MDI1LzA1L011c3Qt/RG8tVGhpbmdzLWlu/LUxpc2Jvbi1mb3It/Rmlyc3QtVGltZXJz/LmpwZw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://www.bontraveler.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Must-Do-Things-in-Lisbon-for-First-Timers.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"In the Graça neighborhood, Tasca do Jaime d’Alfama is a friendly spot far from the tourist trail. On Saturday and Sunday afternoons, the place is a good spot to hear amateur singers who are getting established. Any occasion is a good one to enjoy a bifana, a grilled thinly sliced pork that is unique to Lisbon’s food culture.|Just a short train ride from Lisbon, a day trip to Cascais offers a change of pace and scenery. The town’s streets are lined with small shops and cafés, and its harbor provides a clear view of the Atlantic. You can visit the Museu Condes de Castro Guimarães in the morning, then walk along the coast to Boca do Inferno (Devil’s Mouth), where waves crash against the cliffs. In the afternoon, spend time on Praia da Rainha or cycle along the coastal path toward Guincho Beach.|They serve this unique cherry liqueur drink with or without candied cherries. The locals come here to enjoy it, standing in the street. A great way to start the evening in Lisbon! ... There is no shortage of viewpoints from “miradouros” (belvederes) in Lisbon.|Visiting Lisbon for the first time? Don’t miss my first-timer’s guide to Lisbon, ultimate 3-day Lisbon itinerary, and recommendations for where to stay, the best boutique hotels and best restaurants in Lisbon!\"\nhash: 16c23d733d31b636\nembed_ref: bontraveler.com-PMb\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
